summary: Under appreciated things about Park jimin #3
title: Under appreciated things about Park jimin #3
body:
His intelligence.

Usually when people talk about JM, they tend to mention his EQ first, and it’s not hard to see why. Indeed, his kindness and ability to read social situations makes this area of his personality shine brightly. However, his academic background is not less important and is worth appreciating just as much as his EQ.

  • He was his class president for over 9 years (isn’t that a super long time?) I touched briefly on his leadership qualities here, and it comes around in this area as well. Being class president means putting yourself out there, taking more responsibilities than the rest, organizing events, solving problems in his class, and more.
  • He was an honor student, being the only one to get 100 in his math test on 2nd grade among dance majors. 
  • Valedictorian (highest ranked student - no.1 overall) - (For more, please check out this amazing thread!)

Apparently his grades were so up there, that his father wanted him to continue in the field and become a government official. To his surprise, JM laid his eyes on dancing instead. With the help of his teacher who noticed his dancing skills, he was able to persuade his father and go on that path. His favorite subjects were Math, Art, Chemistry and PE. 

I can go on and on about his achievements, but I want to see more people talk about this. He’s not just kind and friendly, he’s also smart, reads books on his free time and is always open and willing to learn new things. He barely mentions all of this though. He is a silent achiever, basically the poster child for house Slytherin with his ambitious, leader-like and hard working personality. 

Along with his cryptic tweets, hidden messages (I might do a separate post about that), he has this air about him, as if he knows. 

JM is very clever. Let’s not forget that.

summary: Dark Water by missberrycake (19k) Pairing: Jung Hoseok | J-Hope/Kim Taehyung | V “Alright, so you and your friends were attacked...
caption:
Dark Water by missberrycake (19k)

Pairing: Jung Hoseok | J-Hope/Kim Taehyung | V

“Alright, so you and your friends were attacked by a demon, or a spirit, or something. You don’t know.” He raised an eyebrow at Jimin. “It was dark.”

Jimin’s cheeks pinked. “It was dark.”

Park Jimin turns up at Namjoon’s house, asking for help. Full of tales of ghosts, demons and the paranormal, Namjoon doesn’t believe a word of it. He’s dragged along for the ride, however, when friends Hobi and Taehyung fall for it hook, line and sinker.

It seems, though, that there might be more to this ghost story than Namjoon first thought
